"use strict";(self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website=self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website||[]).push([[322],{91326:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"Security Engineer \u2013 Cloud and Kubernetes","subtitle":"Permanent employee, full-time - Norway - Oslo","id":"423396","jobDescriptions":["\\n                            <name>The team and your role </name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                <p><em>Location: Remote/On-site/Hybrid</em><br><br>We are looking for a security engineer with knowledge of modern security practices to join us and be part of our team defending our communication services. While many companies take security for granted, WG2 realizes that the security work we do is vital for our platform and our customers. &nbsp;Because Working Group Two realizes that good security is critical in the current competitive landscape, we have the freedom to take a proactive approach and can plan longer-term and bigger tasks rather than only reacting to immediate needs.</p><p>This is a unique opportunity to help shape modern telecommunications.</p><h3><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\"><strong>You will</strong></span></h3><ul><li><p>Adopt and build security solutions for identifying and preventing misconfigurations across AWS and Kubernetes</p></li><li><p>Make security an integral part of our CI/CD pipeline</p></li><li><p>Provide security guidance to Engineering and Product teams through threat modeling</p></li><li><p>Build security metrics and alerts</p></li></ul><h2><strong><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\">We\'re looking for someone who</span></strong></h2><ul><li><p>Learns quickly and is comfortable with ambiguity</p></li><li><p>Likes to learn about new technologies and acquire new skills&nbsp;</p></li><li><p>Holds themselves and others to a high bar when working with production</p></li><li><p>Is able to design and write high-quality code and configuration in a relevant language (e.g. Golang, Python, Terraform).</p></li></ul><h2><span style=\\"font-size:14px;\\"><strong><span style=\\"font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\\">Who you\'ll work with</span></strong></span></h2><p><br>A dedicated security team.</p><h2><span style=\\"font-size:14px;font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\\"><strong>What\'s it like to work at Working Group Two?</strong></span></h2><ul><li><p>We are a small team that values getting things done in a professional manner</p></li><li><p>We encourage curiosity and creativity</p></li><li><p>We aim to create a warm and welcoming work environment</p></li><li><p>We treat our coworkers well and offer competitive benefits to employees</p></li><li><p>We work remotely but have offices in Norway (Oslo and Trondheim) and Sweden, engineering hubs in Germany and Japan, and employees in 11 countries.</p></li><li><p>To learn more about \u201cthe way we roll\u201d we suggest you have a quick read through https://www.wgtwo.com/blog/were-all-grownups-here</p></li></ul><br>\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        ","\\n                            <name>Our company culture</name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                If you join us, you\u2019ll get the trust and freedom needed to make a big impact in the telco industry.&nbsp;<br>Since we\u2019re solving telco problems in a modern way, we recruit from various industries and have people that used to work at Telenor, Google, Microsoft, Spotify,&nbsp;<br>AWS among others. We promise that you\u2019ll be surrounded by friendly, motivated and highly skilled coworkers. We have a culture of transparency&nbsp;<br>and openness, and oftentimes we call ourselves a \u201cstart-up for grown-ups\u201d. We know where we\u2019re going, and with a lot of trust in each other, we\u2019ll pave the way&nbsp;<br>there together.<br><br>We\u2019re a distributed company with offices in Oslo, Trondheim and Stockholm, a hub in Germany, as well as some remote colleagues in a total of 11 countries.&nbsp;<br>The Covid-19 pandemic forced a lot of companies to change how they think, but for us it confirmed that our remote-friendly and transparent approach goes a long way.&nbsp;\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        "]}')}}]);